# Top-level dependencies for Pipulate
# This file is used by pip-compile to generate requirements.txt
# pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt --upgrade
# NOTE: TO AVOID THE ERROR: AttributeError: 'InstallRequirement' object has no attribute 'use_pep517'
# pip-compiling right now requires downgrading:
# RUN THIS: pip install --upgrade pip==25.2
# then re-install pip-tools then do the compile command.

# Here's the procedure for when things get stubborn.

# 1. exit
# 2. rm -rf .venv
# 3. nix develop .#quiet
# 4. pip install --upgrade pip==25.2
# 5. pip install --upgrade pip-tools
# 6. pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt --upgrade --max-rounds 500
#    Make sure the new thing actually made it to requirements.txt
# 7. git add requirements.txt (& commit & push)

